&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;CAD Engineering Designer&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Glendale, AZ&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Fortune 100 Food &amp;amp; Beverage Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(FuseGlobal has worked with this company for 20 years)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial term: &lt;/strong&gt;11 months (position expected to run longer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: 24 hours per week. &lt;/strong&gt;Part Time, three days per week 8:00 am - 4:30 pm (hybrid: one or two days on site) ; Willingness to travel to other factory and vendor locations is required, with travel expectations of 10-20%.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CAD Engineering Designer will utilize AutoCAD 2025 to provide preliminary design and drafting support for Factory Engineering, focusing on Architectural, Mechanical, and Electrical disciplines. This role includes assisting in the preparation of supporting documents for capital investment proposals in collaboration with factory and Group Engineering teams. The CAD Drafter will need to be proficient in AutoCAD 2D, 3D, and Autodesk Inventor, enabling the creation of industrial drawings for equipment tooling, layouts, process flow sheets, P&amp;amp;IDs, and fabrication details. Additionally, the CAD Drafter will prepare specifications to meet comprehensive design responsibilities and may work with BIM360 and AutoCAD Construction Cloud (ACC). The ability to assemble bid packages following AIA specifications and execute small projects is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that factory key drawings are kept up-to-date and properly archived at the factory or site.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the factory engineers and operations teams in establishing layouts and flow sheets during the conceptual and basic design phases of projects related to new products, new process lines, and line improvement projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support various large print requests for factory events, VIP visits, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose and define different alternatives to support the Early Management principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support engineers or other factory functions with technical concepts and basic design for operational projects, including machine or tooling design using AutoDesk Inventor to support Early Management principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update and coordinate technical guidelines and specifications related to drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and ensure standards for engineering drawings are consistently applied in the factory in accordance with Group Engineering drawing standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the organization of Engineering Drawing and manuals in both paper and electronic format. Support project turnover from Engineers to ensure manuals and drawings are properly archived for Engineering and Maintenance activities. Digitize drawings as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide training to factory engineers or any third-party contractors engaged in the preparation of factory project or operational drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage small building improvement/upgrade projects with contractor supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Engineering Department with SAP and NIMT Administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be willing to travel to other factories and vendor sites as required to support resident factory project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent is required, college degree in a related field, preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional certification in industrial design/drafting, specifically using AutoCAD, preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technically competent and highly proficient in AutoCAD 2D/3D to

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Digital Content Planner&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;St. Louis, MO&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Fortune 100 Food &amp;amp; Beverage Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(FuseGlobal has worked with this company for 20 years)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial term: &lt;/strong&gt;12 months (position expected to run longer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;Mon-Thur onsite, Friday WFH. 8 AM-4:30 PM&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***This is a pet friendly environment***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Digital Content Planner, you’ll partner with Digital Strategists and creative team members on the execution of all digital campaign activations through the timely handoff and delivery of creative files, detailed asset organization and auditing, maintaining accurate file specifications, and data reporting. We’ll count on you to stay on top of the fast-paced work environment and ever-evolving digital landscape while keeping a heavy focus on website, search, eCRM, social, display, video content designed to drive business goals and brand objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for all content execution across website, social (organic and paid), online video, digital banners, and retailer assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and complete social content calendars, website update request forms, paid media traffic sheets, and other digital handoff processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Project Managers to ensure all deadlines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee accurate content deliverables, from project brief to launch, including checking specifications and requirements, providing final creative assets to outside vendors, and conducting QA reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a key contact for media agencies, ensuring all digital creative assets are trafficked accurately ahead of launch and communicating timely updates to all clients, partners, and teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Digital Strategists and analytics counterparts on pulling data and insights for owned digital properties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist Digital Strategists in the creation of campaign kickoff documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong agility and attention to detail skills while working cross-functionally with creative and account teams on multiple projects.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or High School diploma with 4 years of professional experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of professional experience including 1+ years of experience working in a digital and/or social marketing field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience in digital campaign activations including website, email, social, video and display.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required: Microsoft Office/SharePoint/Excel/PowerPoint/ Google Analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred: Scanova/Sprinklr/ Meta Business Manager/ Workfront/ Adobe Suite (photoshop).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
