&lt;p class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Long-Term Engagements:&lt;/strong&gt; Our project-based roles are full-time, long-term engagements, with an average tenure of 3.5 years. Many of our team members have been with us for over a decade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Selective, Impactful Opportunities:&lt;/strong&gt; We work only on roles that are career-enhancing and built to last, ensuring your time is spent on meaningful, high-value projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;• &lt;strong&gt;Transition to Permanent Roles:&lt;/strong&gt; Some project-based engagements transition into permanent roles with our clients—a success we’re thrilled to celebrate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation and Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Unlike other project-based staffing companies, FuseGlobal offers comprehensive compensation and benefits to support your well-being and success:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Competitive hourly rate/salary + Overtime (if applicable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;401(k) Retirement Savings Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Disability Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Connect with Us! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;By applying here, you’ll be considered for future FuseGlobal opportunities and be among the first to hear about exciting roles that match your experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;HR Operations Associate&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;St. Louis, MO&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Fortune 100 Food &amp;amp; Beverage Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(FuseGlobal has worked with this company for 20 years)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial term: &lt;/strong&gt;12 months (position expected to run longer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;Monday to Thursday onsite, Friday WFH&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The HR Operations Associate plays a key role in ensuring the efficient and effective functioning of HR Operations. This includes responding to routine HR inquiries, providing system expertise, and serving as a trusted liaison with HR Centers of Excellence. The role also involves supporting various HR initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regularly interface with key stakeholders, including factory and field personnel, HR Operations, HR Business Partners, and HR Services teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provides administrative support to multiple factories across the organization, including data entry, personnel records management, and training coordination. Maintain strict confidentiality and demonstrate a strong understanding of applicable federal HR and payroll regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Process employment-related transactions such as employee life-cycle events, pay changes, and other sensitive forms and records. Ensure timely maintenance and distribution of employee information, policies, procedures, and related communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support a continuous learning environment by documenting and sharing knowledge across the team. Demonstrate administrative excellence by consistently meeting or exceeding departmental goals and contribute ideas to improve team effectiveness and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine HR transactions and correspondence in alignment with customer requests and requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process and maintain documentation related to employee lifecycle activities, including employment changes, and other HR records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage employee lifecycle transactions in a timely manner, including job requisitions, position changes, organizational updates, and separation or retirement processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess customer needs, gather relevant information, and provide guidance or resolution options while navigating multiple HR systems and applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support high-volume workloads for assigned client groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a communication liaison by identifying and sharing departmental trends, concerns, and improvement opportunities with HR Leadership, Factory HR, and HR partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate regularly with HR teams through ongoing communication, participation in team calls, and support with reporting and escalations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, maintain, and continuously improve departmental processes and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong working relationships with key stakeholders and team members to support efficient and effective processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure the accuracy and integrity of employee records, including completion of Form I-9 verifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct New Hire Orientations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or GED equivalent required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in human resources or related discipline preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
