&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Industrial Services Process Engineer&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Glendale, AZ&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Fortune 100 Food &amp;amp; Beverage Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(FuseGlobal has worked with this company for 20 years)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial term: &lt;/strong&gt;11 months (position expected to run longer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;M-F 8:00am - 4:30pm&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Process Engineer – Utilities &amp;amp; Water Treatment provides technical leadership for site utility and water systems, including steam generation, cooling, water treatment, wastewater treatment, and water reuse. This role optimizes system performance, improves reliability, supports safe and compliant operations, and leads process improvement from concept through commissioning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Performance &amp;amp; Continuous Improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead process design, analysis, troubleshooting, and optimization for boilers, steam, cooling, chilled water, water treatment, wastewater, and water reuse systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and execute debottlenecking opportunities to improve capacity, reliability, efficiency, and operating cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze performance data, identify losses and failure modes, and implement corrective actions using structured methods such as DMAIC, root cause analysis, and standard work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Controls, Documentation &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain control narratives, functional specifications, SOPs, P&amp;amp;IDs, operating procedures, alarms, interlocks, critical parameters, and operating limits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with automation, operations, maintenance, quality, and EHS teams to implement and optimize safe, reliable, and compliant control strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation required for audits, inspections, regulatory compliance, and internal standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Projects, Commissioning &amp;amp; Reliability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support capital projects through scope development, design reviews, equipment selection, FAT/SAT execution, commissioning, start-up, and performance verification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve process and equipment issues during implementation to achieve design capacity, reliability, quality, and compliance objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor utility KPIs including capacity, uptime, water usage, chemical usage, energy efficiency, and operating cost; support maintenance strategies that improve reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Leadership &amp;amp; Training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert for utility and water treatment systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical coaching, training, and troubleshooting support to operations and maintenance teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support site improvement initiatives, standardization efforts, and cross-functional problem solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Chemical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–8+ years of experience in process engineering, utilities, water/wastewater treatment, food and beverage manufacturing, or industrial manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with process improvement, commissioning, start-up, troubleshooting, and cross-func

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Laboratory Quality Technician&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Leonia, NJ&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Fortune 100 Food &amp;amp; Beverage Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;(FuseGlobal has worked with this company for 20 years)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial term: &lt;/strong&gt;6 months&amp;nbsp; (position expected to run longer)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;Monday-Friday; 1st shift&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;​Under the direction of the Supervisor Quality Lab Services, Manager Quality Lab Services the Laboratory Technician Quality Services is responsible for performing routine laboratory support functions, cleaning of glassware, and general housekeeping.&amp;nbsp; Non-routine duties are performed in a learning capacity under direct supervision.&amp;nbsp; Responsibilities are focused on less complex testing and support functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform qualitative analysis of samples.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct routine and laboratory support functions, such as collecting samples, preparation of media, reagents and standard solutions, stocking and distributing supplies and equipment and collecting, washing and storing glassware. &amp;nbsp;As required, maintains related notes and records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Records data, performs calculations, analyzes, &amp;nbsp;reports, and authorizes results. &amp;nbsp; Performs peer review of data and provides critical analysis of laboratory systems. &amp;nbsp;Keeps management apprised of progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritizes workload and meets scheduled timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informs Supervisor of equipment and supply needs required to avoid delays in testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reports results of assignments and maintains and performs related record keeping in compliance with approved regulatory policies and standards to meet quality and accuracy requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows and complies with all appropriate SOP’s, QP’s, GMP’s and safety and health requirements as applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate good housekeeping practices to minimize analytical mix-ups, potential laboratory contamination and safety hazards. &amp;nbsp;Understanding and handling of hazardous materials and waste using proper and safe techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists higher level technical and scientific personnel as needed to learn more advanced techniques, equipment, instrumentation and procedures specific to the Quality Control Department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display ability in interpreting and evaluating atypical/OOS results and immediately report them to Supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Show versatility and be able to work as a part of a team when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibit positive attitude regarding work and responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively within teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to focus on details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to maintain effectiveness during major changes in work tasks or the work environment; adjusting effectively to within new work structures, processes, requirements or cultures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or general education degree (GED) required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in chemistry or other closely related discipline preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0 to 1 years of laboratory experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good time management skills and have the ability to meet deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be willing to meet tight deadlines and work overtime, if required.&lt;/li&gt;
